        "text":"Ask anybody and they could almost surely tell you the tale of Harry Potter and the Philosopher\u2019s Stone.\nBut this is not a story about the boy who lived.\nThis is the story of a courageous girl named Eleanor Oakheart, and how she lived.\n\nThe Oakhearts were␀ <family type>␀\n\nAnd their daughter...\n\nEleanor, or Elly as her friends called her, just turned 11. At the moment, she sat with her house in Hogwarts's grand dining hall. She could not help but recall the eventful year so far.\n\nWhen she was chosen by the Sorting Hat to join Gryffindor, where only the bravest and most daring of magical folk were chosen. Or when a mountain troll roamed and terrorised the halls of Hogwarts.\n\nOf course, she had heard that the Boy Who Lived, had enrolled in Hogwarts the same time as her. Just like everyone else, she was curious about dear Mr Potter. So when Harry tried to sneak off with Ron Weasley and Hermione Granger, she followed them.",
